subject: [Lab 09] Q5: Make a List
content:
Q5: Make a List

Please post all questions you have below concerning Q5: Make a List in the follow-ups.

If you are stuck on this question, feel free to read through the follow-up responses to see if you can draw any ideas from them.

follow-ups.feedback: thanks. I got it before your help. Thank you so much. there are some funny questions

threads.question: For unlocking the test cases, why shouldn't cdr of c be (2 1)?

follow-ups.feedback: There's a difference between lists of the form `(a b c)` and lists of the form `(a (b c))`
